node.text:
“Perhaps most indelibly, Fanone offered his take on the rioters who’d heeded his pleas for mercy. “A lot of people have asked me my thoughts on the individuals in the crowd that helped me,” he drawled. “I think the conclusion I’ve come to is, like, thank you”—here he paused and squinted—“but f-ck you for being there.”

I posted the accompanying article from @time magazine, which is absolutely worth the read, on my Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres and in my stories.

node.text:
“Kids remain at the lowest risk of any group for hospitalization and death. And kids are at higher risk of hospitalization now than ever before in the pandemic.
One of the rare blessings of the pandemic has been that children have proved uniquely able to deal with the attacks of SARS-CoV-2. Their risk of serious illness has always been very, very low. And the available evidence suggests that this has not changed. COVID-NET, which is a CDC sample of hospitals, shows that the rate of hospitalizations for kids has varied in the pandemic from about .3 hospitalizations per 100,000 to 1.5 hospitalizations per 100,000. That rate is rising quickly now, but it remains within the historical envelope of the pandemic in the United States—at about 1 hospitalization per 100,000 children. Similar trends hold true for age subgroups such as 0–4, 5–11, and all under 18. And hospitalization rates for children younger than 18 remain considerably lower than the peak hospitalization rates of adults 18–49 (10 in 100,000), 50–64 (28 in 100,000), and 65 and older (72 in 100,000).
That said, the CDC’s COVID-NET data do not cover the whole country—it pulls data from 99 counties across 14 states, representing about 10 percent of the U.S. population. And it has no data from hospitals in the worst-hit state, Florida.”

May be an image of text that says 'Can someone please tell me how separate schools, bus seats, restaurants, churches, and water fountains is segregation but banning unvaccinated people from gyms, theaters, churches, restaurants, and classrooms isn't segregation?'.

node.text:
***It literally takes a full minute, tops, to read the caption and know that these are not my words. Are you new here?***

Who wants to tell her? I guess you can lead a horse to water… God forbid you do something that could possibly prevent someone else from getting sick. Do these ppl not understand this is a private business? If a bakery doesn’t have to make a cake for a gay wedding, a business doesn’t have to let you in if you’re unvaccinated. 🤷🏻‍♀️ Like it or not, that’s their right. Stop begging for oppression. Ain’t nobody oppressing you! 

Y’all need to stop. You do too much. Having to wear a mask and being asked to get a vaccine to hopefully end a pandemic, is not comparable to what happened during segregation. It’s actually a pretty disgusting comparison. 

Earlier I saw someone compare having to wear a mask to Kristallnacht. Like, how? Why?? Stop. It’s gross, and it shows that you have no comprehension and or care or concern of what happened during segregation or Kristallnacht. #FauxPression
